The paper introduces a logical framework for decision making uncertainty that extends both logic programming and stochastic models such as influence diagrams. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories, including artificial intelligence (cs.AI), logic in computer science (cs.LO), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), multiagent systems (cs.MA), and systems and control (cs.SY). However, given the focus on decision making and uncertainty, cs.AI and cs.DM are the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.LO, cs.MA, and cs.SY.
